# Docker build-context excludes. Both image builds use the REPO ROOT as their context
# (services/dashboard/Dockerfile and docker/fp-dev.Dockerfile — see the compose `build.context: .`),
# so EVERYTHING here is otherwise tar'd and sent to the daemon on every build.
#
# Two reasons this file exists:
#   1. CORRECTNESS — `data/pg` is the root-owned (uid 70, mode 700) Postgres data dir; the build
#      context tar can't read it and the build fails with permission-denied. Excluding data/ is what
#      lets `docker compose build dashboard` run directly (no clean-worktree workaround).
#   2. SPEED — experiments/ alone is ~13G of regenerable research output; none of it is COPY'd.
#
# SAFETY: nothing COPY'd by either Dockerfile is excluded. The dashboard image COPYs `rust/`,
# `quantlib/`, `services/dashboard/requirements.txt`, and `services/dashboard/*.py`; fp-dev COPYs
# `rust/`. All of those are kept. rust/target and *.so are build artifacts maturin regenerates from
# rust/ source, so excluding them is safe and shrinks the context.

# Postgres data dir (root-owned, mode 700 -> unreadable by the context tar; this is the build-breaker)
data/

# Regenerable research output / experiment artifacts (~13G, never COPY'd)
experiments/

# Git metadata (worktree .git file + the worktrees dir) — not needed in any image
.git
.worktrees/
.claude/

# Python caches and tooling caches
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.venv/

# Rust build artifacts (the wheel is rebuilt from rust/ source inside the image)
rust/target/
*.so

# Local env / logs (also gitignored)
.env
*.log
